  <section id="Section519671" role="openmfg">
    <title>Breeder Bill of Materials</title>
    <para>A Breeder Item is an Item from which other Items--or
    by-products--are produced. An example would be gravel. A company can put
    gravel through a screening process, using screens of different widths. The
    resulting by-products might be three grades of materials: fine, medium,
    and coarse. Each by-product would be considered a separate Item, having
    been bred from the initial Breeder Item.</para>
    <xi:include href="guiclient/bbom.xml"
                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                xpointer="element(/1)" />
